swL2MgmtMIB.name: swL2MgmtMIB
swL2MgmtMIB.description: The Structure of Layer 2 Network Management Information for the proprietary enterprise.

swDevInfoSystemUpTime.name: swDevInfoSystemUpTime
swDevInfoSystemUpTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the switch entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re-initialization, then this object contains a zero value. This value is in units of seconds.

swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort.name: swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort
swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort.description: The number of ports within this switch. This value is the sum of the ports within this switch.

swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse.name: swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse
swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse.description: The number of ports in this switch connected to the segment or the end stations.

swDevInfoConsoleInUse.name: swDevInfoConsoleInUse
swDevInfoConsoleInUse.description: This usage indication of console system.

swDevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus.name: swDevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus
swDevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus.description: This object is a set of system LED indications. The first three octets is defined as system LED. The first LED is primary power LED. The second LED is redundant power LED. The third LED is console LED. The other octets following the second octets are the logical port LED (following dot1dBasePort ordering). Every two bytes are presented to a port. The first byte is presentd to the Link/Activity LED. The second byte is presented to the Speed LED. Link/Activity LED : The most significant bit is used for blink/solid: 8 = The LED blinks. The second significant bit is used for link status: 1 = link fail. 2 = link pass. Speed LED : 01 = 10Mbps. 02 = 100Mbps. 03 = 1000Mbps. The four remaining bits are currently unused and must be 0.

swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadState.name: swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadState
swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadState.description: status of upload/download control. If the value is 'other', means never firmware updated since device started up.

swDevInfoSaveCfg.name: swDevInfoSaveCfg
swDevInfoSaveCfg.description: This object indicates the status of the device configuration. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. proceeding(2) - the device configuration is saving into the NV-RAM. ready(3) V the device configuration has been ready to save into NV-RAM. failed(4) - The processing of saving device configuration is failed.

swL2DevCtrlStpState.name: swL2DevCtrlStpState
swL2DevCtrlStpState.description: This object can be enabled or disabled spanning tree algorithm during runtime of the system.

swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.name: swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping
swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.description: This object indicates layer 2 Internet Group Management Protocol (IGMP) capture function is enabled or disabled.

swL2DevCtrlRmonState.name: swL2DevCtrlRmonState
swL2DevCtrlRmonState.description: This object can be enabled or disabled RMON.

swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadImageFileName.name: swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadImageFileName
swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadImageFileName.description: The name of the image file to be uploaded/Downloaded from the device to TFTP server when enabling image upload/download function (by writing swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadImage).

swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadImageSourceAddr.name: swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadImageSourceAddr
swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadImageSourceAddr.description: The ip address where been uploaded/Downloaded image file.

swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadImage.name: swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadImage
swL2DevCtrlUpDownloadImage.description: Image file upload/download control. After setting, it will immediately invoke image upload/download function. While retrieving the value of this object, it always returns 'other' normally.

swL2DevCtrlSaveCfg.name: swL2DevCtrlSaveCfg
swL2DevCtrlSaveCfg.description: As the object is set to active, the current device configuration is save into to NV-RAM.If set to normal, do nothing.

swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.name: swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter
swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.description: As the object is set to active, all the statistic counters will be cleared. If set to normal, do nothing.

swL2DevCtrlStpForwardBPDU.name: swL2DevCtrlStpForwardBPDU
swL2DevCtrlStpForwardBPDU.description: This object allow the forwarding of STP BPDU packets from other network device or not when STP is disabled on the device.

swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.name: swL2DevAlarmNewRoot
swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.description: When the device has become the new root of the Spanning Tree, this object decide whether to send a new root trap.

swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.name: swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange
swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.description: This object determine to send a trap or not when the switch topology was changed. If the object is enabled(3), the topologyChange trap is sent by the device when any of its configured ports transitions from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. For the same port tranition, the device doesn't send the trap if this object value is disabled or other.

swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.name: swL2DevAlarmLinkChange
swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.description: This object determine to send a trap or not when the link was changed. If the object is enabled(3), the Link Change trap is sent by the device when any of its ports link change. The device doesn't send the trap if this object value is disabled or other.

swL2PortInfoTable.name: swL2PortInfoTable
swL2PortInfoTable.description: A table that contains information about every port.

swL2PortInfoEntry.name: swL2PortInfoEntry
swL2PortInfoEntry.description: A list of information for each port of the device.

swL2PortInfoPortIndex.name: swL2PortInfoPortIndex
swL2PortInfoPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortInfoUnitIndex.name: swL2PortInfoUnitIndex
swL2PortInfoUnitIndex.description: Indicates ID of the unit in the device

swL2PortInfoType.name: swL2PortInfoType
swL2PortInfoType.description: This object indicates the connector type of this port.

swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.name: swL2PortInfoLinkStatus
swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.description: This object indicates the port link status.

swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.name: swL2PortInfoNwayStatus
swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.description: This object indicates the port speed and duplex mode.

swL2PortCtrlTable.name: swL2PortCtrlTable
swL2PortCtrlTable.description: A table that contains control information about every port.

swL2PortCtrlEntry.name: swL2PortCtrlEntry
swL2PortCtrlEntry.description: A list of control information for each port of the device.

swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2PortCtrlPortIndex
swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex.name: swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex
swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex.description: Indicates ID of the unit in the device

swL2PortCtrlAdminState.name: swL2PortCtrlAdminState
swL2PortCtrlAdminState.description: This object decide the port enabled or disabled.

swL2PortCtrlNwayState.name: swL2PortCtrlNwayState
swL2PortCtrlNwayState.description: Chose the port speed, duplex mode, and N-Way function mode.

swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.name: swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState
swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.description: The flow control mechanism is different between full duplex mode and half duplex mode. For half duplex mode, the jamming signal is asserted. For full duplex mode, IEEE 802.3x flow control function sends PAUSE frames and receives PAUSE frames.

swL2PortCtrlAddressLearningState.name: swL2PortCtrlAddressLearningState
swL2PortCtrlAddressLearningState.description: This object decide the address learning state on this port is enabled or disabled.

swL2PortUtilTable.name: swL2PortUtilTable
swL2PortUtilTable.description: A table that contains information of utilization about every port.

swL2PortUtilEntry.name: swL2PortUtilEntry
swL2PortUtilEntry.description: A list of information of utilization for each port of the device.

swL2PortUtilPortIndex.name: swL2PortUtilPortIndex
swL2PortUtilPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortUtilTxSec.name: swL2PortUtilTxSec
swL2PortUtilTxSec.description: Indicates how many packets transmitted per second.

swL2PortUtilRxSec.name: swL2PortUtilRxSec
swL2PortUtilRxSec.description: Indicates how many packets received per second.

swL2PortUtilUtilization.name: swL2PortUtilUtilization
swL2PortUtilUtilization.description: This object indicates the port utilization.

swL2FilterAddrMaxSupportedEntries.name: swL2FilterAddrMaxSupportedEntries
swL2FilterAddrMaxSupportedEntries.description: Maximum number of entries in the MAC address filtering table (swL2FilterAddrCtrlTable).

swL2FilterAddrCurrentTotalEntries.name: swL2FilterAddrCurrentTotalEntries
swL2FilterAddrCurrentTotalEntries.description: Current applied number of entries in the MAC address filtering table.

swL2FilterAddrCtrlTable.name: swL2FilterAddrCtrlTable
swL2FilterAddrCtrlTable.description: This table defines information for the device to filter packets with specific MAC address (either as the DA and/or as the SA). The MAC address can be a unicast address or a multicast address. This table has higher priority than both static FDB table and IGMP table. It means that if a MAC address appears on this table also appears on the static FDB table, the device will use the information provide by this table to process the packet.

swL2FilterAddrCtrlEntry.name: swL2FilterAddrCtrlEntry
swL2FilterAddrCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific unicast/multicast MAC address for which the switch has filtering information.

swL2FilterAddrMacIndex.name: swL2FilterAddrMacIndex
swL2FilterAddrMacIndex.description: This object indicates a unicast/multicast MAC address for which the switch has filtering information. But if the swL2FilterAddrState = src-addr then the object can not be a multicast MAC address.

swL2FilterAddrState.name: swL2FilterAddrState
swL2FilterAddrState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. dst-addr(2) - recieved frames's destination address are currently used to be filtered as it meets with the MAC address entry of the table. src-addr(3) - recieved frames's source address are currently used to be filtered as it meets with the MAC address entry of the table. dst-src-addr(4) - recieved frames's destination address or source address are currently used to be filtered as it meets with the MAC address entry of the table. invalid(5) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table.

swL2StaticVlanTable.name: swL2StaticVlanTable
swL2StaticVlanTable.description: A table containing static configuration information for each VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management.

swL2StaticVlanEntry.name: swL2StaticVlanEntry
swL2StaticVlanEntry.description: Static information for a VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management.

swL2StaticVlanIndex.name: swL2StaticVlanIndex
swL2StaticVlanIndex.description: A value that uniquely identifies the Virtual LAN associated with this entry.

swL2StaticVlanName.name: swL2StaticVlanName
swL2StaticVlanName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this VLAN.

swL2StaticVlanType.name: swL2StaticVlanType
swL2StaticVlanType.description: The type of VLAN, distinguished according to the policy used to define its port membership.

swL2StaticVlanProtocolId.name: swL2StaticVlanProtocolId
swL2StaticVlanProtocolId.description: The protocol identifier of this VLAN. This value is meaningful only if swL2StaticVlanType is equal to byProtocolId(3). For other VLAN types it should have the value none(0).

swL2StaticVlanIpSubnetAddr.name: swL2StaticVlanIpSubnetAddr
swL2StaticVlanIpSubnetAddr.description: The IP subnet address of this VLAN. This value is meaningful only if rcVlanType is equal to byIpSubnet(2). For other VLAN types it should have the value 0.0.0.0.

swL2StaticVlanIpSubnetMask.name: swL2StaticVlanIpSubnetMask
swL2StaticVlanIpSubnetMask.description: The IP subnet mask of this VLAN. This value is meaningful only if rcVlanType is equal to byIpSubnet(2). For other VLAN types it should have the value 0.0.0.0.

swL2StaticVlanUserDefinedPid.name: swL2StaticVlanUserDefinedPid
swL2StaticVlanUserDefinedPid.description: When swL2StaticVlanProtocolId is set to userDefined(16) in a protocol-based VLAN, this field represents the 16-bit user defined protocol identifier. Otherwise, this object should be zero.

swL2StaticVlanEncap.name: swL2StaticVlanEncap
swL2StaticVlanEncap.description: This value is meaningful only if swL2StaticVlanProtocolId is set to userDefined(16). Otherwise, this object should be un-used(5). If If this set to ethernet2(2), the Detagged Frame uses Type-encapsulated 802.3 format. If this set to llc(3), the Detagged Frame contains both a DSAP and an SSAP address field in the positions. If this set to snap(4), the Detagged Frame is of the format specified by IEEE Std. 802.1H for the encoding of an IEEE 802.3 Type Field in an 802.2/SNAP header.

swL2StaticVlanUserPriority.name: swL2StaticVlanUserPriority
swL2StaticVlanUserPriority.description: User priority level. This value is meaningful only if swL2StaticVlanType is set to byIpSubnet(2) or byProtocolId(3).

swL2StaticVlanEgressPorts.name: swL2StaticVlanEgressPorts
swL2StaticVlanEgressPorts.description: The set of ports which are permanently assigned to the egress list for this VLAN by management. The default value of this object is a string of zeros of appropriate length.

swL2StaticVlanUntaggedPorts.name: swL2StaticVlanUntaggedPorts
swL2StaticVlanUntaggedPorts.description: The set of ports which should transmit egress packets for this VLAN as untagged. The default value of this object for the default VLAN is a string of appropriate length including all ports. There is no specified default for other VLANs.

swL2StaticVlanStatus.name: swL2StaticVlanStatus
swL2StaticVlanStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2StaticVlanIpSubnetArpClassId.name: swL2StaticVlanIpSubnetArpClassId
swL2StaticVlanIpSubnetArpClassId.description: This object indicates the ARP classification ID. If the swL2StaticVlanType is not byIpSubnet(2), this value must be 0. If the swL2StaticVlanType is byIpSubnet(2), the range of this object is 1 to 4094. This object is useful when create the first IpSubnet entry, and not allow to modify.

swL2VlanPortTable.name: swL2VlanPortTable
swL2VlanPortTable.description: A table containing per port control and status information for VLAN configuration in the device.

swL2VlanPortEntry.name: swL2VlanPortEntry
swL2VlanPortEntry.description: Information controlling VLAN configuration for a port on the device.

swL2VlanPortIndex.name: swL2VlanPortIndex
swL2VlanPortIndex.description: An unique index used to identify a particular port in the system.

swL2VlanPortPvid.name: swL2VlanPortPvid
swL2VlanPortPvid.description: The PVID, the VLAN ID assigned to untagged frames or Priority- Tagged frames received on this port.

swL2VlanPortIngressChecking.name: swL2VlanPortIngressChecking
swL2VlanPortIngressChecking.description: When this is enabled(3) the device will discard incoming frames for VLANs which do not include this Port in its Member set. When disabled(2), the port will accept all incoming frames.

swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.name: swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries
swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.description: Maximum number of entries in the trunk configuration table (swL2TrunkCtrlTable).

swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.name: swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries
swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.description: Current actived number of entries in the trunk configuration table.

swL2TrunkCtrlTable.name: swL2TrunkCtrlTable
swL2TrunkCtrlTable.description: This table specifys which ports group a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.name: swL2TrunkCtrlEntry
swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.description: A list of information specifies which ports group a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkIndex.name: swL2TrunkIndex
swL2TrunkIndex.description: The index of logical port trunk. The trunk group number depend on the existence of unit and module.

swL2TrunkName.name: swL2TrunkName
swL2TrunkName.description: The name of logical port trunk.

swL2TrunkMasterPort.name: swL2TrunkMasterPort
swL2TrunkMasterPort.description: The object indicates the master port number of the port trunk entry. When using Port Trunk, you can not configure the other ports of the group except the master port. Their configuration must be same as the master port (e.g. speed, duplex, enabled/disabled, flow control, and so on).

swL2TrunkMember.name: swL2TrunkMember
swL2TrunkMember.description: Indicate how many number of ports is included in this Trunk. The trunk port number depend on the existence of module. The maximum number of ports is 4 for one trunks.

swL2TrunkFloodingPort.name: swL2TrunkFloodingPort
swL2TrunkFloodingPort.description: The object indicates the flooding port number of the port trunk entry. The first port of the trunk is implicitly configured to be the flooding port.

swL2TrunkState.name: swL2TrunkState
swL2TrunkState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disabled(2) - the port trunk disabled. enabled(3) - the port trunk enabled. invalid(4) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table.

swL2TrunkBPDU8600InterState.name: swL2TrunkBPDU8600InterState
swL2TrunkBPDU8600InterState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disabled(2) - the trunk member doesn't send BPDU. enabled(3) - the trunk member can send BPDU.

swL2TrunkAlgorithm.name: swL2TrunkAlgorithm
swL2TrunkAlgorithm.description: This object configures to part of the packet examined by the switch when selecting the egress port for transmitting load-sharing data. This feature is only available using the address-based load-sharing algorithm.

swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.name: swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort
swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.description: This object indicates switch which port will sniff another port. A trunk port member cannot be configured as a target Snooping port. The port number is the sequential (logical) number which is also applied to bridge MIB, etc.

swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress
swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.description: The represent the ingress into the source port packet to sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress
swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.description: The represent the egress from the source port packet to sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortState.name: swL2MirrorPortState
swL2MirrorPortState.description: This object indicates the port mirroring state. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disabled(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. enabled(3) - this entry is reside in the table.

swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.name: swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans
swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.description: Maximum number of Vlans in the layer 2 IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan.name: swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan
swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan.description: Maximum number of multicast ip group per Vlan in the layer 2 IGMP information table (swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable).

swL2IGMPCtrlTable.name: swL2IGMPCtrlTable
swL2IGMPCtrlTable.description: The table controls the Vlan's IGMP function. Its scale depends on current VLAN state (swL2VlanInfoStatus). If VLAN is disabled mode, there is only one entry in the table, with index 1. If VLAN is in Port-Base or 802.1q mode, the number of entries can be up to 12, with index range from 1 to 12.

swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.name: swL2IGMPCtrlEntry
swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.description: The entry in IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable). The entry is effective only when IGMP capture switch (swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping) is enabled.

swL2IGMPCtrlVid.name: swL2IGMPCtrlVid
swL2IGMPCtrlVid.description: This object indicates the IGMP control entry's VLAN id. If VLAN is disabled, the Vid is always 0 and cannot be changed by management users. If VLAN is in Port-Base mode, the Vid is arranged from 1 to 12, fixed form. If VLAN is in 802.1q mode, the Vid setting can vary from 1 to 4094 by management user, and the Vid in each entry must be unique in the IGMP Control Table.

swL2IGMPQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPQueryInterval
swL2IGMPQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP Host-Query packets are transmitted on this switch.

swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.name: swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime
swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.description: The maximum query response time on this switch.

swL2IGMPRobustness.name: swL2IGMPRobustness
swL2IGMPRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses.

swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval
swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages.

swL2IGMPHostTimeout.name: swL2IGMPHostTimeout
swL2IGMPHostTimeout.description: The timer value for sending IGMP query packet when none was sent by the host in the LAN. The timer works in per-VLAN basis. Our device will be activated to send the query message if the timer is expired. Please reference RFC2236-1997.

swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.name: swL2IGMPRouteTimeout
swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.description: The Router Timeout is how long a host must wait after hearing a Query before it may send any IGMPv2 messages.

swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.name: swL2IGMPLeaveTimer
swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.description: When a querier receives a Leave Group message for a group that has group members on the reception interface, it sends Group-Specific Queries every swL2IGMPLeaveTimer to the group being left.

swL2IGMPQueryState.name: swL2IGMPQueryState
swL2IGMPQueryState.description: This object decide the IGMP query enabled or disabled.

swL2IGMPCurrentState.name: swL2IGMPCurrentState
swL2IGMPCurrentState.description: This object indicates the current IGMP query state.

swL2IGMPCtrlState.name: swL2IGMPCtrlState
swL2IGMPCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disabled(2) - IGMP funtion is disabled for this entry. enabled(3) - IGMP funtion is enabled for this entry.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable
swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.description: The table contains the number current IGMP query packets which is captured by this device, as well as the IGMP query packets sent by the device.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry
swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP query information, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled.

swL2IGMPInfoVid.name: swL2IGMPInfoVid
swL2IGMPInfoVid.description: This object indicates the Vid of associated IGMP info table entry. It follows swL2IGMPCtrlVid in the associated entry of IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.description: This object indicates the number of query packets received since the IGMP function enabled, in per-VLAN basis.

swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.description: This object indicates the send count of IGMP query messages, in per-VLAN basis. In case of IGMP timer expiration, the switch sends IGMP query packets to related VLAN member ports and increment this object by 1.

swL2IGMPGroupTable.name: swL2IGMPGroupTable
swL2IGMPGroupTable.description: The table containing current IGMP information which captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled. Note that the priority of IGMP table entries is lower than Filtering Table, i.e. if there is a table hash collision between the entries of IGMP Table and Filtering Table inside the switch H/W address table, then Filtering Table entry overwrite the colliding entry of IGMP Table. See swL2FilterMgmt description also.

swL2IGMPGroupEntry.name: swL2IGMPGroupEntry
swL2IGMPGroupEntry.description: Information about current IGMP information which captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled.

swL2IGMPVid.name: swL2IGMPVid
swL2IGMPVid.description: This object indicates the Vid of individual IGMP table entry. It shows the Vid of IGMP report information captured on network.

swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.name: swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr
swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.description: This object is identify group ip address which is captured from IGMP packet, in per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPMacAddr.name: swL2IGMPMacAddr
swL2IGMPMacAddr.description: This object is identify mac address which is corresponding to swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr, in per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPPortMap.name: swL2IGMPPortMap
swL2IGMPPortMap.description: This object indicates which ports are belong to the same multicast group, in per-Vlan basis. Each multicast group has a octect string to indicate with port map. The most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'(Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant). The 4 octets is represent one unit port according its logic port. If the unit less 32 port, the other port don't care just fill zero.

swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount.name: swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount
swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount.description: This object indicate how much report packet was receive by our device corresponding with this entry from IGMP function enabled, in per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPForwardTable.name: swL2IGMPForwardTable
swL2IGMPForwardTable.description: The table containing current IGMP forwarding information which captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled. Note that the priority of IGMP table entries is lower than Filtering Table, i.e. if there is a table hash collision between the entries of IGMP Table and Filtering Table inside the switch H/W address table, then Filtering Table entry overwrite the colliding entry of IGMP Table. See swL2FilterMgmt description also.

swL2IGMPForwardEntry.name: swL2IGMPForwardEntry
swL2IGMPForwardEntry.description: Information about current IGMP forwarding information which captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled.

swL2IGMPForwardVid.name: swL2IGMPForwardVid
swL2IGMPForwardVid.description: This object indicates the Vid of individual IGMP table entry. It shows the Vid of IGMP report forward information captured on network.

swL2IGMPForwardGroupIpAddr.name: swL2IGMPForwardGroupIpAddr
swL2IGMPForwardGroupIpAddr.description: This object is identify group ip address which is captured from IGMP packet, in per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPForwardPortMap.name: swL2IGMPForwardPortMap
swL2IGMPForwardPortMap.description: This object indicates which ports are belong to the same multicast group, in per-Vlan basis. Each multicast group has a octect string to indicate with port map. The most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'(Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant). The 4 octets is represent one unit port according its logic port. If the unit less 32 port, the other port don't care just fill zero.

swL2IGMPRPTable.name: swL2IGMPRPTable
